// FP DP3: `dot(vec3, vec3)` → `DP3R R0, f[COL0], weights;` (opcode 0x05).
//
// The IR for `dot(vcol.rgb, weights)` includes an explicit
// VecShuffle [xyz] step that narrows the vec4 to vec3.  Since NV40's
// DP3 naturally reads only X/Y/Z of its source operands, the shuffle
// is a no-op at the hardware level — our lowering aliases identity-
// prefix shuffles through without emitting an extra instruction.
void main(
    float4 vcol       : COLOR,
    uniform float3 weights,
    out float4 color  : COLOR)
{
    color = dot(vcol.rgb, weights);
}
